main event: A UFO sighting was reported near Homestead Air Force Base in Florida on May 30, 1956, lasting approximately 30 minutes.
interesting points: The object was described as either circular, elliptical, or spherical and measured between 30 and 60 feet in diameter., It exhibited behavior of hovering before rapidly flying off., Observations indicated the object had bright or luminous colors., The object was observed by multiple military personnel including pilots and a chief dispatcher., The object was reported to possibly be a balloon or an astronomical object but lacked sufficient data for definitive evaluation.
witness description: military personnel including pilots and a chief dispatcher
